# Practical 3 – Directory, Process, Pipe and Protection Commands

## AIM
To execute Linux commands related to directory management, process
control, pipes and protection.

## DIRECTORY COMMANDS
mkdir test        – create directory "test"  
cd test           – change current directory  
cd ..             – go to parent directory  
rmdir test        – remove empty directory  
ls -l             – list files with permissions and size  

## PROCESS CONTROL COMMANDS
ps                – display running processes  
sleep 10 &        – run sleep command in background  
kill <pid>        – terminate process with given process id  

## PIPE AND REDIRECTION
ls | wc -l                     – count number of files in directory  
cat file.txt | grep "OS"       – show lines containing word "OS"  

## PROTECTION COMMANDS
chmod 755 file.txt             – change permission of file  
chown user file.txt            – change owner of file  
chgrp group file.txt           – change group of file  

## RESULT
Directory, process, pipe and protection related commands were
successfully used in Linux.
